  <summary>3/5/1998--Introduced.
Volunteer Organization Safety Act of 1998 - Prohibits the U.S. Government from requiring, as a condition of completing a State and Federal criminal history check on a volunteer through the national criminal history background check system, that the requesting entity supply such person's fingerprints.</summary>
